TBT Bot – Privacy Policy
Last updated: February 2026
TBT Bot (“the Bot”) is a custom Discord bot created for use within the TB Server community. This Privacy Policy explains what information the Bot collects, how it is used, and how it is protected.

1. Information the Bot Collects
The Bot may collect and store the following limited information:
a. User-Triggered Commands
When users interact with the Bot (for example: !tyrone, /warn, /request-kick, /rqsong), the Bot may record:
Discord User ID


Username / Tag


Content of the command


Timestamp of the interaction


b. Moderation System Data
For features such as strikes, warnings, or moderation requests, the Bot may store:
User ID of the reported user


Reason for the action


Strike count or disciplinary history


Admin decisions or approvals


This information is stored only to make moderation tools function correctly.
c. Optional Song Requests
Song requests may include:
Song name / link


User ID of the requester



2. How the Information Is Used
The Bot only uses collected data for:
Moderation features (warnings, strikes, mutes, bans)


Processing kick/ban approval workflows


Handling song requests


Responding to user commands


Operating channel-specific features (ex: Tyrone AI replies)


Improving user experience within the server


No data is shared with any third parties.

3. Data Storage and Retention
All data is stored securely on the server hosting the Bot.


Strike/moderation data may be retained until manually cleared by an admin.


Song requests may be deleted after processing.


No long-term logging or analytics are performed.



4. What the Bot Does NOT Collect
The Bot does NOT collect:
Passwords


Email addresses


Phone numbers


IP addresses


Private messages (DMs)


Payment information


Any personal info outside your Discord profile


The Bot cannot read your private DMs.

5. Data Sharing
The Bot does not sell, trade, or share any user data with:
Advertisers


Third-party companies


Other Discord servers


Any external services (except Spotify API only when you explicitly trigger a song request addition)



6. User Permissions & Control
If you are a user in the server, you have the right to:
Ask what data the Bot has stored about you


Request deletion of moderation history (at staff discretion)


Stop using the Bot at any time by leaving the server


Admins may manually clear or reset Bot data upon request.

7. Security
Steps are taken to keep data safe:
Limited access to the Bot and its hosting environment


Use of secure API keys and encrypted communication


No public exposure of stored data


However, no system is 100 percent secure.
By using the Bot, you acknowledge this.

8. Changes to This Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Changes will take effect immediately when posted.

9. Contact
If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact the server owner or an administrator in the Discord server.


